From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Leithner <christian_leithner@comcast.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jan 2026 17:40:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Yocto: Use legacy pip resolver to speed up dependency resolution

The new pip resolver (pip >= 20.3) uses backtracking which can take 15+ minutes
for complex dependency trees like pigweed. Use the legacy resolver which is much
faster for Yocto builds where we have tightly controlled dependencies.

Generated by Copilot AI
Signed-off-by: Christian Leithner <christian_leithner@comcast.com>

---
 pw_build/py/pw_build/pip_install_python_deps.py | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/pw_build/py/pw_build/pip_install_python_deps.py b/pw_build/py/pw_build/pip_install_python_deps.py
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/pw_build/py/pw_build/pip_install_python_deps.py
+++ b/pw_build/py/pw_build/pip_install_python_deps.py
@@ -76,6 +76,12 @@ def main(
       FileNotFoundError: if a Python wheel was not found when using pip install
           with --require-hashes.
     """
+    # YOCTO: Use legacy resolver for much faster dependency resolution
+    # The new resolver can take 15+ minutes backtracking through versions
+    if '--use-deprecated=legacy-resolver' not in pip_args:
+        pip_args = ['--use-deprecated=legacy-resolver'] + pip_args
+        _LOG.info('YOCTO BUILD: Using legacy pip resolver for faster builds')
+
     pip_target_dirs: list[Path] = []
 
     py_packages = load_packages([python_dep_list_files], ignore_missing=True)
